<span id="freeTextContainer12232620402675176815">So you think know the story of Little Red Riding Hood, the girl with the unfortunate name and the inability to tell the difference between her grandmother and a member of a different species? Well, then, try your hand at answering these questions:<br/><br/>-Which character (not including Little Red herself) is the most fashion challenged?<br/><br/>-Who (not including the wolf) is the scariest</span>
  <span id="freeText12232620402675176815" style="display:none">So you think know the story of Little Red Riding Hood, the girl with the unfortunate name and the inability to tell the difference between her grandmother and a member of a different species? Well, then, try your hand at answering these questions:<br /><br />-Which character (not including Little Red herself) is the most fashion challenged?<br /><br />-Who (not including the wolf) is the scariest? <br /><br />-Who (not including Granny) is the most easily scared?<br /><br />-Who is the strangest? (Notice we're not "not including" anyone, because they're all a little off.)<br /><br />-Who (no fair saying "the author") has stuffing for brains?<br /><br />Vivian Vande Velde has taken eight new looks at one of the world's most beloved (and mixed-up) stories. You may never look at fairy tales in quite the same way again.</span>
