<div id="review_1921158297" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1921158297" />
    <a title="Felicia Edens" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58888061-felicia-edens"><img alt="Felicia Edens" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1620702621p2/58888061.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1921158297?book_show_action=true">Feb 22, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Felicia Edens" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Felicia Edens" href="/user/show/58888061-felicia-edens">Felicia Edens</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58888061-felicia-edens?shelf=fairy-tales-folklore-fantasy">fairy-tales-folklore-fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1921158297" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6680953998595045710">Vivian Vande Velde, author of “The Rumpelstiltskin Problem”, writes another clever and witty book, this time pointing out how the story of “Little Red Riding Hood” is completely absurd. First, she starts off with the main character’s name, which is, in fact, a name for an article of clothing. In eight short stories, Velde re-writes the tale, giving “Little Red Riding Hood” new depth and humor. Velde’s tidbits of information, such as how, once upon a time, the kingdom ruled the forest so that no </span>
  <span id="freeText6680953998595045710" style="display:none">Vivian Vande Velde, author of “The Rumpelstiltskin Problem”, writes another clever and witty book, this time pointing out how the story of “Little Red Riding Hood” is completely absurd. First, she starts off with the main character’s name, which is, in fact, a name for an article of clothing. In eight short stories, Velde re-writes the tale, giving “Little Red Riding Hood” new depth and humor. Velde’s tidbits of information, such as how, once upon a time, the kingdom ruled the forest so that no one could do anything within them (like cut down a tree) without getting the OK from the King, add a really nice touch to this very good book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6680953998595045710" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


