      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/13014.Vivian_Vande_Velde">About Vivian Vande Velde</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/13014.Vivian_Vande_Velde"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1241839752p3/13014.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/13014.Vivian_Vande_Velde">Vivian Vande Velde
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
909
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer1473243414137159072">Vivian Vande Velde (born 1951, currently residing in Rochester, New York) is an American author who writes books primarily aimed at young adults.<br/><br/>Her novels and short story collections usually have some element of horror or fantasy, but are primarily humorous. Her book <u>Never Trust a Dead Man</u> (1999) received the 2000 Edgar Award for Best Young Adult Novel. She says that she really likes to write for</span>
  <span id="freeText1473243414137159072" style="display:none">Vivian Vande Velde (born 1951, currently residing in Rochester, New York) is an American author who writes books primarily aimed at young adults.<br /><br />Her novels and short story collections usually have some element of horror or fantasy, but are primarily humorous. Her book <u>Never Trust a Dead Man</u> (1999) received the 2000 Edgar Award for Best Young Adult Novel. She says that she really likes to write for children. She likes to do school talks to children. She does many book conventions and also gives writing classes.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1473243414137159072" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
</div>

